# Requirements source of truth

## Authoritative docs (read before claiming “done”)

- **`docs/project/MASTER_PROPOSAL_TODO.md`** — living checklist vs `docs/archive/PROPOSAL.md` (section **“Current snapshot (where we left off)”** for the latest delivery summary + evidence pointers)
- **`docs/REQUIREMENTS_TRACEABILITY.md`** — definitions of Done / Partial / Deferred

Do **not** treat informal summaries, old status markdown, or chat as the contract.

## Language to avoid

- Do not describe delivery as “enough,” “mostly,” “good enough,” or “essentially complete.”
- Use the vocabulary in **`REQUIREMENTS_TRACEABILITY.md`**: **Done**, **Partial** (with documented limitation), **Not started**, **Deferred** (with ADR or explicit backlog row).

## When you close or change a requirement

- Update **`MASTER_PROPOSAL_TODO.md`** in the **same** change (checkboxes, `[x]` / `[~]` / `[ ]`, backlog table).
- Add a short **evidence** pointer (file path, route, or workflow name), not vague claims.

## Out-of-scope / deferred

- If work is intentionally **not** implementing a PROPOSAL item, say so and add or update a row in **`MASTER_PROPOSAL_TODO.md`** or an ADR under `docs/project/` so scope does not silently drift.
